<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<example xml:id="sample-AT2"><title>AT2</title>
<statement>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
Find the standard matrix for the linear transformation <m>T: \IR^3\rightarrow \IR^4</m> given by
<me>T\left(\left[\begin{array}{c} x \\ y \\ z \\  \end{array}\right] \right) = \left[\begin{array}{c} -x+y \\ -x+3y-z \\ 7x+y+3z \\ 0 \end{array}\right].</me>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
Let <m>S: \IR^4 \rightarrow \IR^3</m> be the linear transformation given by the standard matrix
<me>\left[\begin{array}{cccc} 2 &amp; 3 &amp; 4 &amp; 1 \\ 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 &amp; -1 \\ 3 &amp; -2 &amp; -2 &amp; 4 \end{array}\right].</me>
Compute <m> S\left( \left[\begin{array}{c} -2 \\ 1 \\ 3 \\ 2\end{array}\right] \right) </m>.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</statement>
<solution>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
Since
                <md>
                    <mrow>
T\left(\left[\begin{array}{c} 1 \\ 0 \\ 0  \end{array}\right]\right) &amp;= \left[\begin{array}{c} -1 \\ -1 \\ 7 \\0\end{array}\right]
                    </mrow>
                    <mrow>
T\left(\left[\begin{array}{c} 0 \\ 1 \\ 0 \end{array}\right]\right) &amp;= \left[\begin{array}{c} 1 \\ 3 \\ 1 \\0 \end{array}\right]
                    </mrow>
                    <mrow>
T\left(\left[\begin{array}{c} 0 \\ 0 \\ 1 \end{array}\right]\right) &amp;= \left[\begin{array}{c} 0 \\ -1 \\ 3 \\ 0  \end{array}\right],
                    </mrow>
                </md>
the standard matrix for <m>T</m> is <m> \left[\begin{array}{ccc} -1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\ -1 &amp; 3 &amp; -1 \\ 7 &amp; 1 &amp; 3  \\ 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \end{array}\right] </m>.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
<me>
S\left(\left[\begin{array}{c} -2 \\ 1 \\ 3 \\ 2 \end{array}\right] \right) = -2S(\vec{e}_1)+S(\vec{e}_2)+3S(\vec{e}_3)+2S(\vec{e}_4)
                </me>
                <me>
= -2 \left[\begin{array}{c} 2 \\ 0 \\ 3 \end{array}\right] + \left[\begin{array}{c} 3 \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{array}\right] + 3 \left[\begin{array}{c} 4 \\ -1 \\ -2 \end{array}\right]+2\left[\begin{array}{c} 1 \\ -1 \\ 4 \end{array}\right] 
= \left[\begin{array}{c} 13 \\ -4 \\ -6\end{array}\right]. </me>
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</solution>
</example>